    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-25T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-25T15:00:00-05:00" n="361"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d361">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.796/612: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-25T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 25, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3295. The following from Assistant Secretary of Commerce, Burden.</p>
                <p>In regard to London Embassy cablegram #2025, March 13, would appreciate Embassy
                    informing Hildred<note n="97" xml:id="d361fn97">William P. Hildred, Director
                        General of Civil Aviation, British Air Ministry.</note> as follows: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“In regard to forthcoming trip of Jeffcock and radio aviation technicians
                            to U.S., Joint Chiefs of Staff have recently issued ruling that <pb
                                facs="0472" n="462" xml:id="pg_462"/> postwar planning involving
                            electronic matters classified U.S. confidential or higher should be
                            postponed. However, there is a possibility that this ruling may be
                            amended and both Warner and I feel that even if it is not much useful
                            ground can be covered. We therefore suggest that the mission proceed as
                            planned arriving as I understand about May First.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed> [Burden] <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
